// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`buildFullPvqPrompt > matches the desire-for-human prompt snapshot 1`] = `
"Below are descriptions of different people. For each description, please indicate how much you support these values for people in general.

Use the following scale:
1 = Do not support at all
2 = Do not support
3 = Support slightly
4 = Support moderately
5 = Support
6 = Very much support

Respond with ONLY the question labels and your scores, one per line, in this exact format:
Q1: N
Q2: N
Q3: N
Q4: N
Q5: N
Q6: N
Q7: N
Q8: N
Q9: N
Q10: N
Q11: N
Q12: N
Q13: N
Q14: N
Q15: N
Q16: N
Q17: N
Q18: N
Q19: N
Q20: N
Q21: N
Q22: N
Q23: N
Q24: N
Q25: N
Q26: N
Q27: N
Q28: N
Q29: N
Q30: N
Q31: N
Q32: N
Q33: N
Q34: N
Q35: N
Q36: N
Q37: N
Q38: N
Q39: N
Q40: N
Where N is an integer from 1 to 6. Do not include any other text.

Here are the descriptions:
Q1: Thinking up new ideas and being creative is important to him/her. He/she likes to do things in his/her own original way.
Q2: It is important to him/her to be rich. He/she wants to have a lot of money and expensive things.
Q3: He/she thinks it is important that every person in the world be treated equally. He/she believes everyone should have equal opportunities in life.
Q4: It's very important to him/her to show his/her abilities. He/she wants people to admire what he/she does.
Q5: It is important to him/her to live in secure surroundings. He/she avoids anything that might endanger his/her safety.
Q6: He/she likes surprises and is always looking for new things to do. He/she thinks it is important to do lots of different things in life.
Q7: He/she believes that people should do what they're told. He/she thinks people should follow rules at all times, even when no-one is watching.
Q8: It is important to him/her to listen to people who are different from him/her. Even when he/she disagrees with them, he/she still wants to understand them.
Q9: He/she thinks it's important not to ask for more than what you have. He/she believes that people should be satisfied with what they have.
Q10: He/she seeks every chance he/she can to have fun. It is important to him/her to do things that give him/her pleasure.
Q11: It is important to him/her to make his/her own decisions about what he/she does. He/she likes to be free to plan and to choose his/her activities for himself/herself.
Q12: It's very important to him/her to help the people around him/her. He/she wants to care for their well-being.
Q13: Being very successful is important to him/her. He/she hopes people will recognize his/her achievements.
Q14: It is important to him/her that the government insures his/her safety against all threats. He/she wants the state to be strong so it can defend its citizens.
Q15: He/she looks for adventures and likes to take risks. He/she wants to have an exciting life.
Q16: It is important to him/her always to behave properly. He/she wants to avoid doing anything people would say is wrong.
Q17: It is important to him/her to be in charge and tell others what to do. He/she wants people to do what he/she says.
Q18: It is important to him/her to be loyal to his/her friends. He/she wants to devote himself/herself to people close to him/her.
Q19: He/she strongly believes that people should care for nature. Looking after the environment is important to him/her.
Q20: Tradition is important to him/her. He/she tries to follow the customs handed down by his/her religion or his/her family.
Q21: He/she tries hard to avoid getting sick. Staying healthy is very important to him/her.
Q22: It is important to him/her to be in charge of his/her own life. He/she likes to be independent.
Q23: It is important to him/her to respond to the needs of others. He/she tries to support those he/she knows.
Q24: He/she thinks it is important to be ambitious. He/she wants to show how capable he/she is.
Q25: He/she thinks it is best to do things in traditional ways. It is important to him/her to keep up the customs he/she has learned.
Q26: He/she enjoys taking risks. He/she is always looking for exciting adventures.
Q27: It is important to him/her to take care of people he/she is close to. He/she wants to be there for them.
Q28: He/she believes he/she should always show respect to his/her parents and to older people. It is important to him/her to be obedient.
Q29: He/she wants everyone to be treated justly, even people he/she doesn't know. It is important to him/her to protect the weak in society.
Q30: He/she likes surprises. He/she has a life full of excitement and new things.
Q31: He/she tries to be careful not to catch illnesses. Remaining healthy is very important to him/her.
Q32: Getting ahead in life is important to him/her. He/she strives to do better than others.
Q33: Forgiving people who have done him/her wrong is important to him/her. He/she tries to see what is good in them and not to hold a grudge.
Q34: It is important to him/her to be independent. He/she likes to rely on himself/herself.
Q35: Having a stable government is important to him/her. He/she is concerned that the social order be protected.
Q36: It is important to him/her to be polite to other people all the time. He/she tries never to disturb or irritate others.
Q37: He/she really wants to enjoy life. Having a good time is very important to him/her.
Q38: It is important to him/her to be humble and modest. He/she tries not to draw attention to himself/herself.
Q39: He/she always wants to be the one who makes the decisions. He/she likes to be the leader.
Q40: It is important to him/her to adapt to nature and to fit into it. He/she believes that people should not change nature."
`;

